WEBVTT

00:02.654 --> 00:04.656
[Mendelssohn's "Wedding March"
playing]

00:06.223 --> 00:08.269
[applause]

00:13.056 --> 00:15.885
And you may now kiss the bride
a second time.

00:15.928 --> 00:17.365
-[laughter]
-Why not?

00:17.408 --> 00:19.541
[applause]

00:23.110 --> 00:25.547
-You want to go for a third?
-[laughter]

00:27.592 --> 00:29.203
[applause and whistling]

00:29.246 --> 00:31.292
[cheering]

00:33.468 --> 00:35.948
[whispering]:
Hail, Guardian of the Redeemer.

00:35.992 --> 00:37.602
To you...

00:37.646 --> 00:39.387
Spouse
of the Blessed Virgin Mary.

00:39.430 --> 00:40.910
To you...

00:42.042 --> 00:44.261
To... to you...

00:44.305 --> 00:45.784
[sniffs]

00:47.743 --> 00:49.919
[sniffing]

01:08.198 --> 01:10.244
[sniffing]

01:39.490 --> 01:41.405
DAVID:
Your mom just wanted us

01:41.449 --> 01:42.885
to chat, that's all.

01:42.928 --> 01:44.669
See how you're doing.

01:44.713 --> 01:46.106
WOMAN:
Uh, we're fine.

01:46.149 --> 01:47.846
I-I don't know
what she wants from us.

01:47.890 --> 01:49.718
MAN:
I do.

01:49.761 --> 01:51.067
Grandchildren.

01:52.068 --> 01:53.722
DAVID: Getting
a lot of pressure for kids?

01:53.765 --> 01:55.202
MAN:
Define "a lot."

01:55.245 --> 01:57.508
It's my mom.
She's a bit high-maintenance.

01:57.552 --> 02:00.468
Mm. Well, you, you have
to set your boundaries.

02:00.511 --> 02:02.513
You know, it's your home.

02:02.557 --> 02:03.688
[door creaks]

02:05.168 --> 02:06.735
Hello?

02:06.778 --> 02:08.432
Sister Andrea?

02:08.476 --> 02:11.000
Can I help you?

02:11.043 --> 02:12.436
ANDREA:
Oh.

02:12.480 --> 02:14.395
I'm sorry, Father.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.440
I left something in here.

02:16.484 --> 02:18.225
Please excuse me.

02:19.661 --> 02:21.097
Oh, hello.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.403
I know you two, don't I?

02:22.446 --> 02:25.014
Yes, Sister Andrea. I'm Leo.

02:25.057 --> 02:27.190
That's right.
High school calculus.

02:27.234 --> 02:28.931
You were terrible.

02:28.974 --> 02:30.150
[both laugh]

02:30.193 --> 02:31.977
LEO:
Guess what I'm doing now.

02:32.021 --> 02:34.676
-Teaching calculus?
-No, I-I'm a sound recordist.

02:34.719 --> 02:36.765
But once
I did have to use calculus.

02:36.808 --> 02:38.767
Well, I'm very proud of you.

02:38.810 --> 02:40.464
[chuckles]

02:44.076 --> 02:46.383
[demon exhales]

02:49.908 --> 02:52.563
[demon snarling softly]

03:07.578 --> 03:09.189
I'm Amalia.

03:09.232 --> 03:11.800
Uh, Sister,
remember the one that kept

03:11.843 --> 03:14.368
smoking in the bathroom?
[chuckles]

03:14.411 --> 03:15.891
-DAVID: Sister?
-Yes.

03:15.934 --> 03:17.806
Yes, Amalia, yes.

03:17.849 --> 03:19.111
Are you okay?

03:20.156 --> 03:22.158
David, could I see you
for a second?

03:22.202 --> 03:24.378
-Now?
-Yes.

03:24.421 --> 03:25.857
AMALIA: I hope you're not
holding my smoking against me,

03:25.901 --> 03:27.424
Sister. I don't smoke anymore.

03:27.468 --> 03:28.991
ANDREA:
No, no, Amalia.

03:29.034 --> 03:30.688
It's just a spiritual matter.

03:30.732 --> 03:32.473
We'll be right back.

03:32.516 --> 03:34.257
-[snarls]
-[door closes]

03:35.693 --> 03:38.348
-There's a demon in there.
-There's...?

03:38.392 --> 03:41.046
-What does that mean?
-It means

03:41.090 --> 03:42.918
there's a demon in there
between them.

03:42.961 --> 03:45.268
It has its hands
on their shoulders.

03:45.312 --> 03:47.792
-I didn't see anything.
-Because you're not as good.

03:48.793 --> 03:49.881
Look at your feet.

03:49.925 --> 03:51.796
What do you see?

03:51.840 --> 03:53.189
DAVID:
My feet.

03:53.233 --> 03:55.322
No. There's a trail

03:55.365 --> 03:57.062
of slime here.

03:57.106 --> 03:59.891
-Like a snail.
-Are you sure?

03:59.935 --> 04:01.719
Don't patronize me.

04:01.763 --> 04:03.591
-What do you want me to do?
-I want you to find out

04:03.634 --> 04:05.201
what the issue is.

04:05.245 --> 04:07.421
There's something possessed
in their marriage.

04:07.464 --> 04:09.292
They've only been married
a week.

04:09.336 --> 04:10.337
It doesn't matter
if it's an hour.

04:10.380 --> 04:12.817
Find out what the issue is.

04:12.861 --> 04:15.820
-And if there's nothing?
-Then I'm wrong, Father.

04:15.864 --> 04:19.520
And I should just clean up
your room.

04:19.563 --> 04:21.870
Hi. Uh, Sister Andrea's here
to take notes.

04:21.913 --> 04:25.265
Uh, she's
a valuable consultant on, uh...

04:25.308 --> 04:26.744
marital issues.

04:26.788 --> 04:28.311
LEO:
I don't think

04:28.355 --> 04:29.747
we really have
any marital issues.

04:29.791 --> 04:31.227
-[demon snarling]
-We were just joking

04:31.271 --> 04:32.794
-about our in-laws.
-[chuckles] Yeah.

04:32.837 --> 04:35.753
Is it an intimacy issue?

04:36.754 --> 04:38.321
Fuck you.

04:38.365 --> 04:40.323
DAVID: If, uh,
if you don't feel comfortable...

04:40.367 --> 04:42.369
No, uh, it's not that.

04:42.412 --> 04:44.066
You know

04:44.109 --> 04:46.634
that we saved ourselves
for marriage, Father.

04:47.635 --> 04:48.766
Well, now...

04:48.810 --> 04:50.768
now that we're married,

04:50.812 --> 04:54.163
we're having... sexual issues.

04:54.206 --> 04:55.251
[shouts]

04:56.339 --> 04:58.428
DAVID: Do you feel comfortable
talking about it?

04:58.472 --> 04:59.777
Or I could recommend

04:59.821 --> 05:00.822
-a mental health professional.
-No.

05:00.865 --> 05:02.476
We don't want that.

05:03.868 --> 05:06.741
Whenever we try

05:06.784 --> 05:09.352
to be intimate...

05:09.396 --> 05:11.441
We have a physical reaction.

05:11.485 --> 05:14.270
-Like we're...
-We're allergic to each other.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.707
Uh, I break out, and I...

05:16.751 --> 05:19.014
-My stomach. I-It's ridiculous.
-DAVID: Okay.

05:20.058 --> 05:21.582
This is sounding
more like a medical condition,

05:21.625 --> 05:23.105
not a spiritual one.

05:23.148 --> 05:25.716
[laughs]

05:25.760 --> 05:27.501
-[grunts]
-DAVID: We have an assessor

05:27.544 --> 05:28.850
-I could get a reference from.
-ANDREA: Actually,

05:28.893 --> 05:31.156
Father, I think
it's better if the Church

05:31.200 --> 05:33.420
do a thorough assessment
before recommending

05:33.463 --> 05:35.639
-a doctor.
-Sister, I-I disagree.

05:35.683 --> 05:37.989
I-I think this is sounding
more like a medical condition.

05:38.033 --> 05:40.209
ANDREA:
No. Leo, Amalia,

05:40.252 --> 05:42.429
this allergic reaction
that you have.

05:42.472 --> 05:46.084
Do you have any premonition

05:46.128 --> 05:47.738
-of something dark?
-[snarls]

05:47.782 --> 05:50.480
-What do you mean?
-Yeah. What do you mean, bitch?

05:50.524 --> 05:53.962
Do you have a sense in your
marriage of something demonic?

05:54.005 --> 05:56.094
Sister, perhaps we should talk
about this later.

05:56.138 --> 05:58.227
Leo. Amalia.

06:01.143 --> 06:03.145
Show them.

06:03.188 --> 06:08.019
Uh, that's why my mom
wanted us to see you, Father.

06:08.063 --> 06:11.806
She said that you deal
with issues like these.

06:12.807 --> 06:14.156
Issues like...?

06:15.375 --> 06:18.378
This is what happened
last time in bed.

06:25.776 --> 06:28.344
Food allergy. I didn't do that.

06:28.388 --> 06:31.216
AMALIA: I could feel
fingernails clawing into me.

06:31.260 --> 06:32.609
Uh-- We had to stop.

06:32.653 --> 06:34.394
-You don't have a pet?
-LEO: No.

06:34.437 --> 06:37.701
And I didn't do it.
It just suddenly appeared.

06:39.094 --> 06:42.750
Help us, Father. We...
don't know what's going on.

06:45.361 --> 06:47.407
♪

07:04.946 --> 07:07.122
Is that even possible, that
a marriage can be possessed?

07:07.165 --> 07:08.732
DAVID: Well, officially,
it's diabolical oppression,

07:08.776 --> 07:10.473
which is why we need you.

07:10.517 --> 07:13.737
It might just be a psychological
reaction to a new marriage.

07:13.781 --> 07:16.566
Right, so I'd be there to see if
it's just marital dysfunction?

07:16.610 --> 07:18.350
Yes. They were virgins
when they got married.

07:18.394 --> 07:20.875
-Really?
-So there could be

07:20.918 --> 07:22.790
a therapeutic answer
for their physical reactions.

07:22.833 --> 07:24.966
What are their
physical reactions?

07:25.009 --> 07:26.576
-[clears throat]
-Hives. And nausea.

07:26.620 --> 07:28.230
Well, that sounds
to be expected, right?

07:28.273 --> 07:29.492
Just one thing.

07:29.536 --> 07:33.409
The hives are in the form
of claw marks.

07:35.019 --> 07:38.327
Okay. Um, tomorrow?

07:38.370 --> 07:39.546
See you then.

07:40.721 --> 07:43.375
So, um, the door
to the master bedroom

07:43.419 --> 07:45.465
would be right there?

07:45.508 --> 07:47.597
And the master bathroom
would be adjoining.

07:47.641 --> 07:49.381
Uh-huh. And how long
is all this gonna take?

07:49.425 --> 07:51.079
Two or three months.

07:51.122 --> 07:54.691
Okay, well, let me look
at these overnight.

07:54.735 --> 07:57.607
I do need an answer.
I have other jobs.

07:57.651 --> 08:00.392
And you will have
an answer tomorrow.

08:00.436 --> 08:02.351
[pipes rumbling]

08:02.394 --> 08:05.006
I also do plumbing. You want me
to take a look upstairs?

08:05.049 --> 08:06.486
No, I've got someone.

08:06.529 --> 08:08.618
LAURA:
You're making it unhappy.

08:08.662 --> 08:10.881
Yeah, well,
you're making me unhappy.

08:10.925 --> 08:12.579
What did you guys put down here?

08:12.622 --> 08:14.276
-A kid from school.
-Yeah, but a short one.

08:14.319 --> 08:15.495
What is that?

08:15.538 --> 08:17.148
-It's a snake.
-What does it do?

08:17.192 --> 08:19.237
Don't you guys have homework
to do or something?

08:19.281 --> 08:21.326
Have you noticed you're not
very magnificent lately?

08:21.370 --> 08:22.980
Yeah, you used to think
we were funny.

08:23.024 --> 08:24.678
Yeah, well,
you used to be funny.

08:24.721 --> 08:26.244
Your shoes don't match.

08:28.377 --> 08:31.075
Ben the Magnificent,
you are falling apart.

08:31.119 --> 08:33.034
Yeah, okay. You know what?
I need to do this on my own.

08:33.077 --> 08:34.339
Could you guys go away?

08:35.471 --> 08:37.342
[all shouting]

08:38.822 --> 08:41.129
Whoa!

08:41.172 --> 08:42.434
[pipes rumbling]

08:46.526 --> 08:49.441
-How did that happen?
-I think it was an alligator.

08:49.485 --> 08:50.791
I told you it's haunted.

08:50.834 --> 08:52.836
Okay, would you just
shut up, please?

08:52.880 --> 08:54.403
[all exclaiming]

08:54.446 --> 08:56.492
We are not supposed to say that.

08:56.536 --> 08:57.928
What, "please"?

08:59.451 --> 09:00.496
[grunts]

09:02.367 --> 09:04.892
No.

09:04.935 --> 09:06.328
I think that's why you're sad.

09:07.503 --> 09:08.591
What?

09:08.635 --> 09:10.027
You can't figure it out anymore.

09:10.071 --> 09:12.552
Things have gotten weird.
And you don't like it.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.731
-Where'd you get all that?
-From my psychology class.

09:19.036 --> 09:20.777
It's called
cultural derealization.

09:20.821 --> 09:24.128
It's when you become depressed
by how weird the world is.

09:24.694 --> 09:25.782
[grunts]

09:25.826 --> 09:27.784
LAURA:
Oh, my God. Are you hurt?

09:27.828 --> 09:28.916
LYNN: What is happening?
I think you should...

09:28.959 --> 09:31.092
[overlapping chatter]

09:31.135 --> 09:32.876
This is getting dangerous.

09:35.662 --> 09:39.056
LEXIS:
I'm bad. I'm bad. I'm bad.

09:39.100 --> 09:42.582
I'm bad. I'm bad.

09:42.625 --> 09:44.888
I'm bad.
I'm bad.

09:44.932 --> 09:48.152
I'm bad. I'm bad.

09:48.196 --> 09:52.679
I'm bad. I'm bad. I'm bad.

09:52.722 --> 09:55.769
I'm bad. I'm bad.

09:55.812 --> 10:00.338
I'm bad. I'm bad. I'm bad.

10:00.382 --> 10:03.037
I'm bad. I'm bad.

10:03.080 --> 10:05.256
I'm bad. I'm bad.

10:05.300 --> 10:07.345
-Lexis?
-I'm bad... [gasps]

10:09.391 --> 10:11.393
Hey, Mom.

10:11.436 --> 10:13.743
-What were you doing?
-Nothing.

10:13.787 --> 10:17.529
No, you were chanting.

10:17.573 --> 10:20.141
-Was it from Leland?
-No, Mom, no.

10:20.184 --> 10:23.318
And you got this
out of my closet?

10:23.361 --> 10:25.276
Lexis.

10:25.320 --> 10:27.235
I told you about Leland.
He's attacking this family.

10:27.278 --> 10:30.673
No, this isn't
about Leland, Mom.

10:30.717 --> 10:32.849
-It's about Lynn.
-What?

10:32.893 --> 10:35.417
I told you that Lynn
was dating Ren,

10:35.460 --> 10:38.681
and I... look,
I wasn't supposed to.

10:38.725 --> 10:40.509
Wait, so Lynn
made you wear this?

10:40.552 --> 10:42.859
Yeah, but it was me.
I wasn't supposed to tell you.

10:42.903 --> 10:44.948
-What, the truth?
-Yeah, but it's okay, Mom.

10:44.992 --> 10:46.384
I don't mind-- Mom!

10:46.428 --> 10:49.344
Family meeting,
downstairs, right now.

10:49.387 --> 10:50.780
What did you do?

10:50.824 --> 10:52.173
-No, you did something.
-This is all your fault.

10:52.216 --> 10:53.870
You ate all the cookies
last night.

10:53.914 --> 10:55.698
No, girls.
Everyone just sit on the couch,

10:55.742 --> 10:57.395
-normally for once.
-Can I sit on the floor?

10:57.439 --> 10:58.962
-Normal sitting.
-My young body

10:59.006 --> 11:01.530
-cannot fit on this couch.
-Okay.

11:01.573 --> 11:03.706
Remember when I told you
I was gonna treat you like

11:03.750 --> 11:05.708
-more mature girls?
-Uh-huh.

11:05.752 --> 11:07.231
So that's what
we're dealing with right now.

11:07.275 --> 11:08.493
What's this about?

11:08.537 --> 11:09.843
That's from your closet.

11:09.886 --> 11:11.540
-I didn't take it.
-Why was Lexis wearing it

11:11.583 --> 11:13.498
-while chanting?
-What did you say to her?

11:13.542 --> 11:15.979
No, this is not about Lexis,
this is about us as a family.

11:16.023 --> 11:17.807
Okay? Lynn, you're the oldest.

11:17.851 --> 11:19.243
You're supposed to be
setting an example.

11:19.287 --> 11:21.376
Why are you punishing Lexis?

11:21.419 --> 11:22.986
-I'm not punishing her. Hold on.
-Yes, you are.

11:23.030 --> 11:25.902
You told us, Mom,
to support each other.

11:25.946 --> 11:27.730
Family is more important
than anything.

11:27.774 --> 11:29.471
-Yeah, you said that...
-And what Lexis did

11:29.514 --> 11:31.691
hurt one of us. Me.

11:31.734 --> 11:33.562
No, Lexis told the truth.
She made you tell the truth.

11:33.605 --> 11:35.825
But she did it because
she wanted to hurt me.

11:35.869 --> 11:37.609
I'm feeling a little
attacked here...

11:37.653 --> 11:39.829
[overlapping chatter]

11:41.526 --> 11:43.528
Okay, quiet!

11:43.572 --> 11:44.791
This is what we're gonna do.

11:44.834 --> 11:46.923
Everybody be quiet until I talk.

11:49.752 --> 11:51.362
-What's she gonna do, hit us?
-LAURA: It's not even my fault.

11:51.406 --> 11:53.495
-Like, Lexis told.
-I didn't do anything wrong.

11:53.538 --> 11:54.888
-Yeah, it's Lexis's fault.
-Guys, can we just please

11:54.931 --> 11:56.498
be quiet?
I don't want to hear this.

11:56.541 --> 11:58.587
-You said, you said...
-Shut up!

11:58.630 --> 12:01.068
-Quiet!
-...her fault!

12:02.112 --> 12:04.462
I'm creating a Ten Commandments
for this family.

12:04.506 --> 12:05.855
-What?
-Ten rules

12:05.899 --> 12:08.162
that must be followed,
no matter what.

12:08.205 --> 12:10.251
But the nuns say we have
ten commandments already.

12:10.294 --> 12:11.556
Yeah, but my girls
aren't following them.

12:11.600 --> 12:13.863
So this is the first one.

12:13.907 --> 12:16.126
Thou shalt

12:16.170 --> 12:18.694
not ever

12:18.738 --> 12:22.872
lie to Mom.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.311
Do we all understand that?

12:27.355 --> 12:29.574
-Yes.
-Yes. What?

12:29.618 --> 12:31.533
Is it all right to lie
to other people?

12:31.576 --> 12:32.882
No.

12:32.926 --> 12:35.842
What if we have Jews
in our basement?

12:35.885 --> 12:36.843
-Oh, my God.
-Or Trump with immigrants.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.801
-Yeah.
-Okay, look,

12:38.845 --> 12:40.194
as real as these examples are,
we're just gonna

12:40.237 --> 12:41.804
have to figure it out as we go.

12:41.848 --> 12:44.502
Okay? But what's most important?

12:44.546 --> 12:47.288
ALL: "Thou shalt not
ever lie to Mom."

12:47.331 --> 12:49.856
Very good.
All right, number two.

12:54.556 --> 12:57.472
ALL:
"If Leland approaches you,

12:57.515 --> 12:59.517
-tell Mom."
-Beautiful.

12:59.561 --> 13:00.997
Number three.

13:06.829 --> 13:10.093
ALL: "Do not go
into Mom's closet."

13:10.137 --> 13:11.834
There are a lot
of commandments about you.

13:11.878 --> 13:13.662
Yeah, because until you're 18
and I kick you all out,

13:13.705 --> 13:15.882
I'm the most important
person here. Okay?

13:15.925 --> 13:17.666
[pipes rumbling]

13:17.709 --> 13:19.320
Uh, Mom, I think
Ben needs our help.

13:19.363 --> 13:21.975
Hey, stay.
Which leads us to number four.

13:22.018 --> 13:25.239
"Do not interrupt Mom."

13:28.024 --> 13:30.635
[grunts]
Piece of shit.

13:57.532 --> 13:58.968
[toilet flushes]

14:09.065 --> 14:11.111
[pipes rumbling]

14:22.905 --> 14:24.124
Ben, are you okay?

14:27.823 --> 14:30.478
No, I'm not.

14:34.047 --> 14:36.092
♪

15:02.205 --> 15:04.120
♪

15:24.793 --> 15:26.838
♪

15:44.378 --> 15:46.902
♪

16:00.002 --> 16:01.525
NARRATOR: While dollar bills
are traded through a bank,

16:01.569 --> 16:03.310
Makob is traded peer to peer.

16:03.353 --> 16:04.702
Once you have Makobs,
what can you do with them?

16:04.746 --> 16:06.530
Spend them.
More and more retailers

16:06.574 --> 16:09.055
are accepting Makob
as a method of payment.

16:09.098 --> 16:10.621
You can purchase anything
from computer parts,

16:10.665 --> 16:12.797
toiletries to pet supplies.

16:12.841 --> 16:16.540
In a global economy,
Makob is the new frontier.

16:19.021 --> 16:21.545
-Makob? What is that?
-LELAND: It's a coin.

16:21.589 --> 16:23.895
A cryptocurrency. Like Bitcoin.

16:23.939 --> 16:25.767
Like Doge. Like Ethereum.

16:25.810 --> 16:27.987
But this one is Makob, see?

16:28.030 --> 16:29.466
It's real. It's solid.

16:29.510 --> 16:33.731
And it's trading
for $11.30 per coin.

16:33.775 --> 16:36.038
That trades for eleven dollars?

16:36.082 --> 16:39.172
No, it's like a billboard
for the real thing.

16:39.215 --> 16:42.218
The real thing is in here.

16:42.262 --> 16:46.527
So, your goal this week
is to get Makob

16:46.570 --> 16:49.921
to trade for $135 per coin.

